Introduction

Gissele (Korean: 지젤; Japanese: ジゼル) was a South Korean girl band. They debuted in August 2000 with their first studio album, "Attractive Goddess". They were made to represent the 21st century, with a new concept of music: a crossover of ballad, funky, techno music based on rock.They presumably disbanded later that same year.
